poem:
The Correctorwock

Twas patchling, and the loggy bits did glimmer,
The slip-sprites frimmed in the stacky flow;
All code did borble with jitter and shimmer,
While lint-birds fluffed their error-brows low.

"Beware the Errorwock, byte-brimmed and gritable;
Beware the Glitchwyrm, loop-twisted and sly;
Mind the Null-gnarl that springs all unmittable,
And shun the sly off-by that slithers by!"

He took his checksum-sword in hand; long whirred the breaker-hum;
He wore a parity-mantle round, stitched thick with fixful might;
And fast he marched through mem-wold mist where malformed functions drum,
To face the bug that gobbled hope and turned the day to night.

The Errorwock did flicker, snap-crash, and spurn the steady probe;
Its stack-keys clanked, its pointers leapt in wild, uncertain arcs;
But through the heap of froth and fog he traced the failing robe,
And with a tidy snick-snack cleaved the tangles of its marks.

Away he patched! The crashwings fell; the log-gnats scurried clear;
The borble calmed, the lint-birds sang, the runtime hummed anew.
"O fixful day! O call-beam bright!" they cheered with flag and cheer,
And home he went, his patch-bag full, his fixes true and true.
